article.description: — Brian Goracke scored 25 points as Montana State beat Northern Colorado 90-81 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Goracke's 25 help Montana State knock off Northern Colorado 90-81
article.linkText: Goracke's 25 help Montana State knock off Northern Colorado 90-81
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- — Brian Goracke scored 25 points as Montana State beat Northern Colorado 90-81 on Saturday night. Goracke was 7 of 10 shooting, including 3 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 8 for 8 from the line for the Bobcats (8-9, 3-1 Big Sky Conference). Brandon Walker scored 22 points while shooting 8 of 11 from the field and 6 for 7 from the line, and added five rebounds and five assists. Eddie Turner III shot 7 for 12, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc to finish with 18 points. Saint Thomas finished with 27 points and eight rebounds for the Bears (9-7, 2-1). Northern Colorado also got 19 points from Brock Wisne. In addition, Dejour Reaves finished with 11 points. The loss snapped the Bears' five-game winning streak. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
